  - Role resource inspected: app/Http/Resources/Role.php returns { id, name }.
- Standard additional responses inferred from Laravel behavior:
  - 200 OK: successful update returns the UserResource wrapped in the typical JSON Resource envelope (single resource is returned as top-level "data": { ... }).
  - 422 Unprocessable Entity: validation errors, with "message" and "errors" (map of field => [messages]).
  - 403 Forbidden: authorization failure message.
  - 401 Unauthorized: unauthenticated access (e.g., no token).
  - 404 Not Found: model binding failure if the {user} does not exist.
  - 500 Internal Server Error: generic server error fallback.
- All schemas are built inline (no $ref), using the exact fields present in the inspected resources. Types and formats are set according to the code (registered_at uses toIso8601String so format: date-time). The response envelope includes "data" with the user object.

